### Base URL
@gateway = http://localhost:8080

### ------------------------------------------------------------
### 1. Health checks
### ------------------------------------------------------------

GET {{gateway}}/actuator/health

###
GET http://localhost:8081/actuator/health

###
GET http://localhost:8082/actuator/health

###
GET http://localhost:8083/actuator/health

### ------------------------------------------------------------
### 2. Create inventory
### Expected: 201 Created
### MongoDB: inventory_items gets productId=101 with available=10 reserved=0
### ------------------------------------------------------------

POST {{gateway}}/api/inventory
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "productId": 101,
  "productName": "iPhone 15",
  "availableQuantity": 10
}

### Check inventory state
GET {{gateway}}/api/inventory/101

### Check availability
GET {{gateway}}/api/inventory/101/availability

### ------------------------------------------------------------
### 3. Create user
### Expected: 201 Created
### MySQL userdb.users gets one record
### ------------------------------------------------------------

POST {{gateway}}/api/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Rahul",
  "email": "rahul@example.com",
  "address": "Bangalore"
}

### Fetch user
GET {{gateway}}/api/users/1

### ------------------------------------------------------------
### 4. Place order
### Expected immediate response: status CREATED
### MySQL orderdb.orders gets one record
### Kafka: order-service publishes to topic order-created
### ------------------------------------------------------------

POST {{gateway}}/api/orders
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": 1,
  "productId": 101,
  "quantity": 2,
  "unitPrice": 49999.00
}

### ------------------------------------------------------------
### 5. Check order after Kafka processing
### Wait 2-5 seconds before running this request
### Expected final status: STOCK_CONFIRMED
### Kafka: inventory-service consumes order-created and publishes stock-updated
### MongoDB: availableQuantity goes 10 -> 8, reservedQuantity goes 0 -> 2
### ------------------------------------------------------------

GET {{gateway}}/api/orders/1

### Orders by user through user-service -> order-service Feign call
GET {{gateway}}/api/users/1/orders

### Orders directly from order-service route through gateway
GET {{gateway}}/api/orders/user/1

### ------------------------------------------------------------
### 6. Negative test: duplicate user
### Expected: error response
### ------------------------------------------------------------

POST {{gateway}}/api/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Rahul",
  "email": "rahul@example.com",
  "address": "Bangalore"
}

### ------------------------------------------------------------
### 7. Negative test: invalid user
### Expected: user not found error
### ------------------------------------------------------------

POST {{gateway}}/api/orders
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": 999,
  "productId": 101,
  "quantity": 1,
  "unitPrice": 49999.00
}

### ------------------------------------------------------------
### 8. Negative test: insufficient stock
### Expected: insufficient stock error
### ------------------------------------------------------------

POST {{gateway}}/api/orders
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": 1,
  "productId": 101,
  "quantity": 100,
  "unitPrice": 49999.00
}
